sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K792010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Yeast exportable Trp-rich peptide w/enhanced import (1)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This composite device produces and '''exports''' a '''Histidine rich''' peptide, that is '''import enhanced''' (thanks to a trojan peptide). This device is intended to be used with '''Yeast chassis''', so it is composed by subparts designed also to be use in yeast.
The high level structure of the device is:
* '''''Kozak''''' consensus sequence for initiation of translation ''(from yeast α-factor mating pheromone (MFα1))'' * '''''Signal''''' peptide that targets the product of the gene for secretion ''(also from yeast α-factor mating pheromone (MFα1))'' * '''''Trojan''''' peptide, to increase internalization in target cell ''(from HIV TAT penetratin)'' * '''''Payload''''': this is the exported '''Histidine''' rich domain of the protein ''(a His-Tag)''
The device's sequence has inherited some useful '''restriction sites''' (''BamHI'' & ''HindIII'') from the parts it's made of.
'''Important note''': this part has been submitted to the registry using a direct synthesis DNA sample, so it does not contain scars from ''BB assembly standard''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gim??nez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TrpZipper2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: '''TrpZipper''' is a small peptide that folds into a beta-hairpin secondary structure. The indole rings of the Trp form a hydrophobic core. The protein is water soluble and monomer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gim??nez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Sequence obtained by retro-translation. Codon and mRNA-secondary structure optimized for yeast.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TAT-trojan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Import enhancer - HIV TAT penetratin (trojan peptide)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Trojan peptides are short sequences that penetrate through the plasma membrane inside the cell without the need of any receptor or endocitosis process [Derossi 1998]. They can be used to increase the efficiency with which a protein enters a cell.
This part is the penetratin from the HIV TAT protein, and has to be used just before the coding sequence of the peptide that you want to be ''import enhanced''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gim??nez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MFa1-Secre
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Secretion tag from yeast α-factor mating pheromone (MFα1)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the secretion signal peptide for the yeast α-mating factor. This signal peptide directs the secretion of the produced protein, and therefore allows for the exportation of it. This peptides are cleaved once the protein is in the lumen of the ER.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gim??nez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Prepro-a-factorHas a Cleavable Signal Sequence [Water et al 1987]

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MFa1-Kozak
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Kozak sequence from yeast α-factor mating pheromone (MFα1)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The Kozak sequence is the eukaryotic analog of the bacterial RBS, it is short sequence that includes the ATG, required for proficient initiation of translation. It is known that the 5???UTR sequence of the MFα1 gene of yeast produces efficient initiation of translation.
This part is that specific region of the MFα1 gene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manuel Gim??nez
